# Claude Sandbox configuration
#
# Copy this file to ~/.config/claude-sandbox/config and uncomment the
# settings you want to override. All defaults below match what the tool
# uses when no config file is present, so you only need this file if you
# want to change something.
#
# This file is sourced by bash; quote values that contain spaces.

# --- Sandbox container -----------------------------------------------------

# Incus image to launch.
#SANDBOX_IMAGE="images:ubuntu/24.04"

# Where the host project directory is mounted inside the sandbox.
#SANDBOX_PROJECT_PATH="/home/ubuntu/project"

# Note: the Claude auth token is NOT configured here — it is read from
# the CLAUDE_SANDBOX_AUTH environment variable at sandbox-create time,
# and forwarded into the sandbox as ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN. See README.

# --- Status reporter -------------------------------------------------------
#
# A small service inside the sandbox watches ~/.claude/sessions/*.json via
# inotify and publishes a JSON payload whenever the aggregated status
# changes, plus a keep-alive every REPORTER_KEEPALIVE seconds so a
# subscriber that comes online late still learns the current state.
#
# Payload: {"sessions":{"<sessionId>":"<status>",...}}.
# Keys are sorted for deterministic dedup. Consumers should key off
# sessionId, not position, so multiple sandboxes can publish to the same
# subscriber without colliding. Identifying info (developer, hostname) is
# intentionally omitted — encode it in the MQTT topic / HTTP URL.
#
# Backends:
#   none    Disable publishing entirely.
#   stdout  Write each payload to the systemd journal (default; use
#           `incus exec <container> journalctl -u claude-status-reporter`
#           to inspect).
#   file    Append each payload as one JSON line to REPORTER_FILE_PATH.
#   mqtt    Publish via mosquitto_pub with -r (retained). Requires the
#           mqtt backend at sandbox-create time (the installer adds
#           mosquitto-clients).
#   http    POST each payload to REPORTER_HTTP_URL.

#REPORTER_BACKEND="stdout"
#REPORTER_KEEPALIVE=60

# --- file backend ----------------------------------------------------------
#REPORTER_FILE_PATH="/var/log/claude-status.jsonl"

# --- mqtt backend ----------------------------------------------------------
# WARNING: public brokers (test.mosquitto.org, broker.hivemq.com, ...) are
# fully public — anyone can subscribe to any topic. If you publish to one,
# pick a topic that is not guessable (e.g. a UUID) and assume the data is
# visible to the world.
#REPORTER_MQTT_HOST="test.mosquitto.org"
#REPORTER_MQTT_PORT=1883
#REPORTER_MQTT_TOPIC=""
#REPORTER_MQTT_USER=""
#REPORTER_MQTT_PASS=""

# --- http backend ----------------------------------------------------------
#REPORTER_HTTP_URL=""
